        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis characterized by epilepsy with myoclonic atonic and bilateral tonic-clonic seizures gait disturbance and language difficulty/delay. Progressive motor and cognitive decline personality disorders myoclonus and visual loss are common clinical features become evident later in the disease progress. Age of onset is typically late-infantile however few juvenile-onset patients are reported."
        },
